Description:
Period Charmer In Prime Location
Centrally located just walking distance to Coburg North Village, Batman station, Coburg North Primary School and Harmony Park, this three bedroom home invites families, couples and investors to enjoy the easy going lifestyle on offer. Set upon a pristinely landscaped block presenting picturesque front and rear gardens, a handsome façade boasts leadlight windows and clinker brick portico entry. The interior is framed by high decorative ceilings within a floor plan comprising spacious open living area with OFP and fully appointed timber kitchen. A pergola covers the large entertaining area while well scaled bedrooms include generous BIRs. Serviced by a central spa bathroom, laundry and second toilet, there's also split system air conditioning, ducted heating, water tank, driveway and a garage.
Insights: 35 Kerferd Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Charismatic Lifestyle With Dual Frontage
Delight in the charismatic charms of this superbly presented three bedroom Federation home and look to the future to explore the myriad of options presented by its generous 371m2 allotment (approx.) boasting dual street frontage. Attractive and set amongst cottage inspired gardens, this appealing home forms a solid base for families from which to enjoy the great range of parks, schools including St Fideles Primary, transport options, local cafes and bustling attractions of Sydney Road that make this pocket so coveted. Lofty ceilings, superb timber floors and picture rails grace spacious bedrooms, two with open fireplaces and BIR's, and extend through expansive informal living. A charming well-appointed kitchen with copious storage oversees the dining area and sunken lounge before spilling to extensive gardens incorporating a delightful alfresco deck. A stylish family bathroom, separate laundry, split systems, ceiling fans and carport with remote door accessed via Hawthorn Street complete this inviting home, ready to enjoy, and boasting a potential packed future.

Description:
Californian Captivation with Extended Excellence
A sensational blend of classic and contemporary, this stunning single-level home provides an idyllic inner-urban family lifestyle with its flexible floorplan, first-class features and prized position with the best of Coburg at your fingertips. Beyond the immaculate front garden and gorgeous facade, discover a premium interior showcasing three main bedrooms (BIRs) and fourth bedroom/lounge, as well as a stylish master ensuite, deluxe family bathroom and separate powder room. Add to this an expansive open-plan living/dining area enhanced by a superb stone-top kitchen with soft-close drawers, glass splashbacks, walk-in pantry, Smeg/Asko appliances and double glazing. Other highlights include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, original lead-light windows and Art Deco ceilings, solid timber/polished concrete floors, solar power, large laundry with ample storage cupboards, 135-bottle cellar and additional attic storage space (via attic ladder). Step outside to a delightful north-facing backyard including entertaining deck with retractable awnings, studio/workshop, water tank and additional off-street parking for two cars and gated driveway (remote-controlled). A short stroll to Anderson Reserve, it offers easy access to popular primary schools (Coburg West and St Fidelis), Coburg's renowned shopping precinct and Sydney Road cafes, as well as trains and trams to the CBD. Perfect! Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Modern, Luxurious Living On A Grand Scale
Commanding & breathtaking from absolutely every angle, this architecturally designed family home comes packed with extras, sparing no expense right throughout. Extremely generous in size measuring approximately 37.65 squares in size and offering a flexible floorplan with bedrooms and bathrooms on both levels and a very handy 2nd living/retreat zone which is high on the priority list for homes of this calibre. Located in one of Melbourne's finest areas, Coburg is situated approximately 9km's from the CBD and with great tram, train & bus transport access and many local parks, schools & shops nearby. This is the one you have been waiting for, call the family and tell them you have found your dream home!
KEY PROPERTY FEATURES:
- Brick veneer house, built in 2005 (approx.)
- Building Size of 37.65 squares (approx.) & land size measuring 424m2 (approx.)
- BEDROOMS: Four large bedrooms featuring grey ironbark polished timber flooring and built in robes, master bedroom boasting a full Ensuite and a fantastic sized walk in robe
- KITCHEN: Fully appointed with 30mm stone benchtops, Neff built in self-cleaning oven, 900mm Smeg 5 burner gas/electric cooktop and rangehood, Miele dishwasher, glass splashback, island bench, double pantry, built in scale, 2nd fridge cavity & great cupboard space
- LOUNGE/MEALS: Sun filled open plan lounge/dining zone featuring surround sound speakers, a Jetmaster gas log open fireplace, split system air-conditioner & double French door access to a wonderful entertainment area
- 2nd LIVING/RETREAT: Spacious open retreat located upstairs with Grey Ironbark polished timber flooring & sliding door access to a lovely balcony to relax in
- STUDY/5th BEDROOM: A very handy space to work from home, study or simply use as a 5th bedroom depending on your needs, featuring Grey Ironbark polished timber flooring & sliding door access to the balcony
- ENSUITE: Tastefully designed complete with single vanity, shower, toilet, bidet & extensive porcelain tiles
- CENTRAL BATHROOMS: Located both upstairs and downstairs, with shower, vanity & toilet. The central bathroom upstairs boasting a bathtub and separate powder room
- HEATING/COOLING: Jetmaster gas log open fireplace, zoned gas ducted heating, Daikin split system air-conditioners & ceiling fans throughout
- LAUNDRY: Full size laundry with double trough, plenty of storage space and external access to the rear yard
- OUTDOORS: Entertain in style with double French door access to an undercover alfresco area complete with extensive timber decking and the option to fully enclose in those cold wintery months with bistro blinds, there is also a low maintenance concreted area at the rear featuring garden shed & clothesline
- PARKING: Double remote entry garage and 2 additional off-street car spaces
- POTENTIAL RENT: $700 - $750 per week
- ADDITIONAL: Alarm system, security system, ducted vacuum system, instantaneous hot water system with temperature control, 2nd additional kitchen in garage with upright 600mm gas cooker/oven & much more!
KEY LOCATION BENEFITS:
- Close proximity to Batman & Coburg train stations, tram access on Sydney Road & bus services nearby
- Coburg is located approximately 9km's from the CBD with terrific City Link, Ring Road and Airport access
Seeing is believing, make sure you come down and inspect this truly magnificent home!
Daniel Imbesi: 0432 615 416
Mark Imbesi: 0418 345 097

Description:
Affordable Entry Into Coveted Pocket!
Original Brick Veneer Home Set In Popular Pocket Offers Nicholson Street Tram, Merri Creek Parklands, Local Schools, Cafes & Shopping All Within a Short Stroll From Your Door Step.
A sizeable 515 SQM (approx.) East/West allotment also benefits from rear Northern light, whilst the R.O.W car access to the lock up garage off The Grove makes parking a dream.
Spacious and solid with high ceilings, three large bedrooms and a separate lounge room flow from the formal entrance & a spacious kitchen / family room overlooking the sunny rear yard.

To put it simply, "A Solid Honest Home Nestled In This Prized Pocket"!

Set within a boutique block of only 7, this 2 bedroom apartment accentuates the plentiful natural light that pervades the interior. Other features include split-system heating/cooling in the lounge. Close to trams, trains, CityLink access and an array of international cuisine along nearby Sydney Road. Boasting modernisation and extension potential (STCA), this neat and tidy two bedroom single fronted timber period home is blessed with character, space and large backyard with rear right-of-way. Description:
That Perfect Start
This young two bedroom townhouse appeals too many. Perfect fit for those first home buyers or investors. Privately positioned as the back townhouse this cleverly design assures all spaces are highly functional and filled with natural light. Contained within an open plan arrangement, the living domain incorporates distinct lounge, dining and study spaces while also leading to an entertaining terrace. The kitchen boasts a full suite of appliances and caesarstone counters. Well scaled bedrooms (mirrored BIRs) share a stylish bathroom, the master also with a courtyard view. Amongst features are split systems throughout, powder room, video intercom, alarm, water tank plus remote garage (internal access) with laundry facilities. Confirming lifestyle advantage is walking proximity to Melville Road tram, Shore Reserve, Coburg West Primary and all covered within the Strathmore School Zone.

Description:
Prepare To Be Surprised
In a boutique Pentridge Village building opposite Coburg Lake, this one bedroom apartment surprises with generous inclusions and high ceilings. Featuring a kitchen geared to entertaining, complete with 900mm appliances including a fan forced electric oven and canopy rangehood, teamed with a black electric cooktop, Fisher & Paykel dishwasher and granite countertops, it has the features you'd hope for in an apartment - and more. The living area flows to a covered terrace, with space to dine alfresco, and four steps below a private courtyard beckons. The large bedroom hosts a wide built-in robe, plus there's an ensuite and a powder room, both with stone topped vanities. A concealed laundry, storage areas, digital inverter air conditioner, panel heating, video intercom and secure garage parking demonstrate the breadth of features on offer. With Pentridge Community Garden just over the road, a bus stop right outside, plus cafes and Sydney Road within a stroll, it's situated to please.
Insights: 3/1 Stockade Avenue, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 26 other 1 bedroom unit in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Brilliant Townhouse With Views And Double-Glazing
Big, bright and boutique, this unique in design two bedroom, two bathroom owner-occupied townhouse benefits from a brilliant northerly orientation and boasts vast double-glazed aspects capturing leafy parkland views.
Secured by intercom and foyer entry, the home's quality, finishes and generous size is immediately evident from the moment you arrive.
Awash with natural light are large open plan living, meals spaces featuring high ceilings, solid hardwood floors and glass sliders opening wide onto a sun-filled balcony where you can take in views of nearby Merri Creek trails and sports precincts.
Adding further appeal for discerning buyers is a well appointed kitchen displaying a host of stainless steel Fisher& Paykel appliances, Bosch dishwasher, abundant storage solutions and stone counter tops, including breakfast bar.
Private accommodation comprises two oversized bedrooms with high ceilings, generous built-in-robes and plush carpet.
Both enjoy modern ensuites and balcony access.
Complemented by three split-system units, guest powder room, European laundry, under stair storage, linen cupboard and secure basement car space and storage cage on title.
Moments from central Coburg shops, markets, cafes, leisure centres, trains and schools, with easy CBD and airport access and only metres from Nicholson Street trams, while Bell Street buses pass the door.
Insights: 7/7-9 Bell Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 73 other 2 bedroom unit in Coburg have recently been sold.
